#############################################
#          Numeter - poller - INSTALL         #
#############################################

# Need : 
  * numeter-common (redis module)
  * python-redis 2.4.9
  * redis >= 2:2.4.14


#===== script numeter-poller

in your server cron : 
  * * * * *   root    /opt/numeter/numeter-poller

Put config file in /etc/numeter :
  vim /etc/numeter/numeter_poller.cfg

===== api python

Depuis les paquets :
  apt-get install python-redis

Depuis les sources : 
  git clone https://github.com/andymccurdy/redis-py
  cd redis-py
  python setup.py install

===== Installation api python
git clone https://github.com/andymccurdy/redis-py
python setup.py install
ou
apt-get install python-redis

Redis need squeeze backport version
redis > 2:1.2.6-1
deb http://backports.debian.org/debian-backports squeeze-backports main
Package: *
Pin: release o=Debian Backports,a=squeeze-backports
Pin-Priority: 200

apt-get install -t squeeze-backports redis-server

Configuration redis client :
bind 0.0.0.0 

===== redis > 2:1.2.6-1

# Debian squeeze
Ajouter les backports :
  deb http://backports.debian.org/debian-backports squeeze-backports main

Pinning : 
  Package: *
  Pin: release o=Debian Backports,a=squeeze-backports
  Pin-Priority: 200

Installation : 
  apt-get install -t squeeze-backports redis-server
